The present study showed that 1O2 has a relatively high contribution to viral inactivation by CAP (Fig. 8d) within 1 min exposure. An identical course of action has been suggested in other reports. According to GuO et al.,50, bacteriophages can be inactivated by plasma through several actions of singlet 1O2. Additionally, the inactivation of feline calicivirus (FCV) and bacteriophages T4 was shown to be most effective by 1O2 which could alter the molecular mass of methionine and oxidizing histidine residues51. Here, we found that 1O2 and h+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
